---
source: crates/runtime/tests/models/search.rs
description: "SELECT id, answer, trunc(score, 3) FROM vector_search(qs, 'second', answer) order by score desc, id LIMIT 4"
---
+---------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| plan_type     | plan                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
+---------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| logical_plan  | Projection: vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).id, vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).answer, trunc(vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score,Int64(3))                                                       |
|               |   Sort: vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score DESC NULLS FIRST, vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).id ASC NULLS LAST, fetch=4                                                                                    |
|               |     Projection: vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).id, vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).answer, trunc(vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score, Int64(3)), vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score |
|               |       TableScan: vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer) projection=[answer, id, score]                                                                                                                                         |
| physical_plan | ProjectionExec: expr=[id@0 as id, answer@1 as answer, trunc(vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score,Int64(3))@2 as trunc(vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score,Int64(3))]                                       |
|               |   SortPreservingMergeExec: [score@3 DESC, id@0 ASC NULLS LAST], fetch=4                                                                                                                                                           |
|               |     SortExec: TopK(fetch=4), expr=[score@3 DESC, id@0 ASC NULLS LAST], preserve_partitioning=[true]                                                                                                                               |
|               |       ProjectionExec: expr=[id@0 as id, answer@1 as answer, trunc(score@2, 3) as trunc(vector_search(qs, Utf8("second"), answer).score,Int64(3)), score@2 as score]                                                               |
|               |         ProjectionExec: expr=[CAST(key@1 AS Int64) as id, answer@0 as answer, 1 - distance@2 as score]                                                                                                                            |
|               |           CooperativeExec                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
|               |             RepartitionExec: partitioning=RoundRobinBatch(3), input_partitions=1                                                                                                                                                  |
|               |               BytesProcessedExec                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
|               |                 CooperativeExec                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
|               |                   S3VectorsQueryExec: limit=100                                                                                                                                                                                   |
|               |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
+---------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
